<quickviewtext name="Quick View">
<![CDATA[
<p>Did you know that insects are the most diverse group of animals on earth? Many insects are either pests or beneficial species that have great importance to the economy, environment, or public health. Students in the Entomology major learn about environmentally sound methods of controlling domestic and agricultural pests as well as ways to increase the productivity of economically useful insects such as honeybees.</p>
]]>
</quickviewtext>
